review_blob: Pretty clean and standard ipa. More on the pale side if theres one. A nice hop aroma and the head poured well. Hint of pine and grassy flavour. No complaints

A pretty refreshing lager. Nothing special about it. Would imagine its for those who are on the fence about craft and are looking to further there brand. Nice golden/yellow colour. Also rather affordable
Fruity & herbaceous characters. Gold/copper colour, murky. Clean mouth and palate feel
beer_name: Matilda Bay Fat Yak Pale Ale
